{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e319c424-fcf7-4bb5-b9f7-57ea9ed40235","content":"It's a straightforward change. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**What this does:**\n- `MSTest.Sdk` defaults to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** — `UseVSTest` was opting you *out* of it.\n- Removing it switches you to the newer runner automatically.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n1. **CLI**: Use `dotnet test` as usual, but the underlying runner changes.\n2. **`--filter`** syntax stays the same.\n3. **`.runsettings`** are still supported.\n4. **Incompatible VSTest adapters** (e.g., custom `ITestDiscoverer`/`ITestExecutor` extensions) won't work — you'll need Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n5. If you use **code coverage** or **TRX logging**, add the corresponding platform extensions:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n   ```\n\nThat single property removal is the only required change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f32da72-f48c-4f9e-a101-eecaba0d3861","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"1BCB:C0207:207B663:23DF759:6A03CE80"},"id":"01a0aaf8-2328-4ac1-92cf-2a2432666653","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:17.528Z","parentId":"909d3957-35fd-4351-b31d-7f758c0ff7d5"}
